\p{This slice draws from the S-tier locked in iter1: \code{captp}, \code{syrup}, \code{zig-syrup-bci}, \code{wycheproof}, \code{property-based-testing}, \code{constant-time-analysis}, \code{zeroize-audit}. From the iter2-shrunk ?-tier: \code{parametrised-optics-cybernetics} (the seal/unseal pair is a bidirectional optic) and \code{bisimulation-game} (against libsignal-rust as reference).}
\p{No dropped ?-tier skill was needed. The tier triage from iter1-2 holds under this slice — first falsification check of the triage itself.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Iter10 patch — sender-cert spec hole}
\p{Iter9 audit found bcf-0065 v1 had no story for how a recipient verifies WHO sent a sealed envelope. Patching now.}

\subtree{
\title{Sender certificate}
\p{A \code{SenderCert} is issued by the registration handler at device-registration time and re-issued before expiry. It binds a sender swissnum to a public identity key, with a typed expiry.}
\pre{\startverb
sender-cert-v1 = <record sender-cert-v1
                    <sender-swiss Bytes>
                    <sender-pub Bytes32>      // Ed25519 pub
                    <issuer Bytes>            // registration handler's swissnum
                    <expiry-ns u64>           // unix nanos
                    <sig Bytes64>>            // Ed25519(issuer-priv, body)
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Effect signature delta}
\pre{\startverb
effect Registry {
  def known_issuer_pub(): Bytes32   // returns the registration handler's Ed25519 pub
}

effect SealedSender {
  def seal(payload: Bytes^1, my_cert: SenderCert, my_id_priv: Bytes^1,
           recipient: SwissNum): SealedEnvelope^1
  def unseal(env: SealedEnvelope^1, my_swiss: SwissNum^1)
           : Result<(SenderCert, Bytes^1)>
}

// In seal():  inner = encode_record("authed-payload", [my_cert, sign(my_id_priv, payload), payload])
//             ct = aead_seal(key, inner, AD = eph_pub ++ recipient.swiss)
// In unseal(): decrypt → parse inner → verify sig under cert.sender_pub
//                                   → verify cert.sig under known_issuer_pub
//                                   → verify cert.expiry > now()
\stopverb}
\p{The cert lives \em{inside} the AEAD ciphertext, not as a separate envelope field. This binds the cert to the recipient (via AEAD's AD = recipient.swiss) and to the payload (same AEAD). Matches Signal's choice for the same reason.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Sender-cert verification — pass criteria delta}
\p{Replace iter7's criterion 3 (bit-identical libsignal vector — falsified in iter9) with:}
\ol{
\li{\strong{3a (validity).} For a freshly issued cert with expiry in the future, \code{unseal} returns Ok(cert, msg) and the cert verifies under \code{known_issuer_pub()}.}
\li{\strong{3b (expiry).} For a cert with expiry-ns in the past, \code{unseal} returns Err(\code{CertExpired}). Test by constructing a cert with expiry = now - 1ns.}
\li{\strong{3c (tampered cert sig).} For a cert with its sig field flipped one bit, \code{unseal} returns Err(\code{CertSigInvalid}).}
\li{\strong{3d (wrong issuer).} For a cert signed by an unknown Ed25519 key, \code{unseal} returns Err(\code{UnknownIssuer}).}
\li{\strong{3' (differential property).} \code{forall msg, recipient, valid_cert: unseal(seal(msg, valid_cert, sender_priv, recipient)) ≡ Ok(valid_cert, msg)}. Under Hypothesis-style generation.}
}
\p{Criteria 3a-d are runnable in iter11 against the Python sketch from iter8 + this cert addition. Criterion 3' is the differential-fuzz that needs both Whisper-λ and a libsignal FFI shim; defer to iter12 or later.}
}

\subtree{
\title{Skill recruitment delta}
\p{Sender-cert work draws additionally from S-tier: \code{implementing-digital-signatures-with-ed25519} (already locked S in iter1), \code{implementing-jwt-signing-and-verification} (S, for the cert-with-expiry pattern). No new tier shifts.}
}
}
